                <head>No. 112.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Williamson</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1875-04-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 30, 1875</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 166.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch, No. 322, of the 23d ultimo has
                    been received. It relates to the attack on the United States consulate at Omoa
                    in July, 1873. You transmit a protocol for the adjustment with the government of
                    Honduras of the questions arising from that proceeding, and also other papers
                    upon the subject. These have all been carefully considered, and the result is an
                    impression that the settlement is as good as the circumstances would allow,
                    especially when the lapse of time since the attack, is taken into account Your
                    course is accordingly approved, and is deemed creditable to your firmness and
                    sagacity and to the sense of justice of that government.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
